caption: At the first moment  you arrive in this restaurant  team give you an agreeable feeling. Very hospitable waiters, it is a good place to to go out with your friends or with your date. Excellent  meals, talented  chief cook and stuff, comfortable  price and professional  service. Warmly recommended.
Best spot to eat some food when in a hurry. The service is rapid, pricing is convenient, excellent vibes. Will come back again
The food and service were beyond our expectations. We absolutely liked the environment of this place. Awesome spot to take my family out for dinner.
Ordered their spicy dry cooked fish fillet and wonton in red chili sauce today. The food is excessively salty and served in meagre amount. Will never order from this restaurant again.
First visit and impressed by the variety on the menu and the complex flavors in what we ordered. Order was filled timely, and service was friendly.
I like the food from here, the portion is really big. Ppl are always nice and helpful here.
Stale and unflavorful food. Made me sick the next day

Delivery gets between 4 and 5 stars. They do a good job with the food and fast delivery. Which makes me want to order more. Also best to call them to place your order than order on Grubhub, especially if you like to customize your order and spice level. They also do ordering on their website. Generous portions. The Sichuan dishes are solid like the dan dan noodles, wontons in chili oil, mapo tofu and twice cooked fish. They wrap the food well for transit. Also don't forget rice which you will have to order separately.

(Translated by Google) I absolutely love this place, go here at least once a week. Friendly staff and amazing food. Chengdu Chicken is my favorite dish.  They are so good, so delicious. I love his spicy chicken.  (Original) I absolutely love this place, go here at least once a week. Friendly staff and amazing food. Chengdu Chicken is my favorite dish.  他们太好了、太吃好了。我爱他的辣子鸡。
The food is always fresh and yummy, employees hands over awesome service. I loved the cleanliness and atmosphere. Will come back again.

This is one of the best regional Chinese restaurants in the area. It is Sichuan, and those are the dishes that shine. They also have well executed versions of regular fare. Don't listen to the haters.

I ordered General Tso and Salt and Pepper Jumbo Shrimp last Saturday. The chicken was stale, dry and hard. It almost made my gums bleed. The same chicken pieces are probably used in other chicken dishes that use fried chicken pieces as their main ingredient like sesame chicken or orange chicken etc. Stay away from these! unless you want to give your teeth a workout. The shrimp was edible, a little towards the bland side, but much fresher than the chicken. I was trying to support local restaurants especially Chinese but this is what I get. I expected better from these prices, which is higher than your corner Chinese takeout. Not worth the money. Please take your business somewhere else.
The food here is terrible, and the portions are too small. The mosquito in wonton soup, too disgusting！！！🤮

I'm so glad they brought back their lunch specials. Their kung pao chicken has such a great taste with fresh veggies.  This is now my favorite Chinese restaurant in Malden when you consider the quality of the food and the cost.
This spot is superb and broad, the menu was enchanting and the rates were very economical. quickly, efficient service and very personal waiters. I highly recommend this place.

(Translated by Google) The taste is good. If you order takeaway, the driver will ask you for a 10% tip. If it is not enough, it will wait for you downstairs. I’m new here, I don’t know if all restaurants are like this.  (Original) 味道很好，如果点外卖的话，司机会问你要10%的小费，不够的话会在楼下等你，要到为止。 我是新来的，不知道是不是所有餐馆都这样。
Its nice

I am so disappointed in the food from this place. Based on the pictures and reviews, this seemed like a good place to order from, but I was wrong. All of the food just tasted salty with no other flavor. The teriyaki chicken didn't even have teriyaki sauce on it, it was just salted chicken on a skewer. The chicken wings tasted like old chicken that had been sitting around for days before being cooked. When I bit into it, there was a disgusting rotten taste close to the bone. The vegetable fried rice also tasted just gross. It seems like the food was tossed together with barely any care and I spent over $70 on this order. Such a waste. I will not be ordering from here again.
VERY tasty dishes here! Definitely a go-to spot, and you can walk here from J Malden Center!
I always order the singapore rice noodles and am very rarely disappointed. The rest of the food is good as well
Worthwhile!  Get the cumin lamb~

I have to give 5 star because the freshness and taste of the food is perfect.  The chef is good. I think it's a tiny bit overpriced so I would consider it a special occasion.
Food was okay. A bit too bland for me. I got the General Gao's chicken and I had to drown it in hot sauce to get some flavor (I asked for extra spicy).

Really bad experience, I ordered a peach oolong milk tea priced 5.49, but the size of the cup is extremely small! And the food priced 15 dollars (main dishes)didn’t come with rice, which is very unreasonable! And they didn’t ask whether you need rice. I have to cook rice after I got the food...
Great food, especially if you're looking for spicy food.  I've had most of the menu now, and they have a lot of great selections.  Service is a little weird, but nothing deal breaking.
Authentic Chineese cuisine (my international Chinese exchange son loves this place and told me so!)
Great place if you know what to order
Review is for the only dish I had at lunch once:  the best Chengdo Chicken and hot and sour soup I've ever had.  Chilies, peppers, garlic ..heaven!

My experiences are all based on takeout/delivery... Tldr; I won’t be going back.  That being said, all 3 of my orders over the past 2 weeks were submitted online which was pretty straightforward. 1st time turned out meh. The spicy chili chicken wings, hot&sour soup, & sichuan wontons were great, but the spicy lamb noodle completely stumped me since the broth had no lamb whatsoever...3/4, ok. 2nd time ordered pork&leek dumplings (meh) and curry chicken (no description online or in pamphlet) which turns out to be thai curry, not japanese. Per menu, item is spicy, but surprise surprise curry was completely bland (not a single chili fleck). 👎🏽 3rd (& final time) ordered general gao’s chicken (no spice) & chengdu chicken (reg spicy) w/ a coworker. As we’re being handed the food, server asks to clarify which order was meant to be “no spice”. Upon which they admitted accidentally switching the two, so could we wait while they “fix” the mistake? Lo and behold, both my coworker and I agreed our orders were still not right after the first couple of bites. In fact, another coworker (who loyally orders chengdu chicken once a week 🤷🏾‍♀️) commented my order “doesn’t look like chengdu chicken”. 😑

I'm happy to see a new business at this location. It's a beautiful restaurant but honestly the service was so-so. The food was good. The egg drop soup was amazing!!  Nice flavored lobster but Very difficult to eat because the server never brought over any utensils. She was no where to be seen and never came to check on our dishes until it was time for the check
Not missing Yenching Restaurant in Harvard Square, Cambridge. Starting today, its the place my whole family will choose to eat Chinese place. Great food. Lunch portion was good. Extremely satisfying.

Our favorite Asian place in the area, even though they no longer deliver to us. Real, authentic Sichuan cuisine, including numbing spice. Must try!
It’s typical for Sichuan dishes to be both spicy and numbing, but the chef at this place seems to go too heavy on the spice that numbs.

Been here several times and unfortunately the food is not that great here. With other asian options popping up in Malden, you can probably find good alternatives. I guess it’s a solid choice if you’re just looking for MALA styled foods.
Best Scihuan food ever in this area.  Hot hidden gem, plus if you eat spicy and pepper flowers.  Yummy licious

Great Sichuan food! I got the Sichuan dried chicken lunch special. Spicy deliciousness! The chef is awesome, he makes an authentic fried rice with a subtle smoke flavor going through it. This is called"breath of the dragon" and very few chefs in America do this! So good!

very good Szechuan food. I've eaten there many times and tried dozens of their dishes and I been disappointed by one - the beef buns which were dry and unappealing. Otherwise everything has been great.
Great, authentic food. Only problem is their limited delivery  location options.
Loved that cheese tea!!!
This is the first place locally that serves authentic Sichuan food.. FINALLY!!!!

Absolutely terrible. I dont mind language barriers, but when I pointed to three items on the menu, only one item came out. Being hungry I ate the beef dish I didnt order. Once I got the check I found out it was veil, which I dont eat. Service was slow and terrible. I wont be back.
pretty authentic, always enjoyed my dining there!

Great food!! I have been looking for a “American Chinese” place that has great flavor and this place has been the best so far! So many places have soggy, flavorless, garbage and this place knocks it out of the park. They have great scallion pancakes, a must order!! My absolute favorite dish is the general gau’s chicken, SO GOOD!! I crave this now because it’s amazing! The lo neon noodles are also fabulous! Egg rolls aren’t bad at all! Try it all because this place rocks!

Delicious Sichuan food. Could be a little spicier to my taste but food was great overall.  The spicy pigs feet noodles were yummy. The iced fruit teas were really good. They tasted so refreshing. The mango dessert was not bad. Service was friendly. The place was nice and clean. Seats were comfortable.  Prices were reasonable.  Be prepared that you may be asked to pay in cash.  I think they take credit cards but we paid cash, no big deal.  Would certainly be back again to try some other dishes.
Awesome seafood. Must try! And cool refreshing drink!
Delicious food and pretty cheap too. Atmosphere is great and music is awesome. Service is always kind and very fast.
Amazing authentic mandarin cuisine. It's like being back in China.
They’ve got cool drinks and desserts for the summer.
The only issue we had was with the teapot. You couldn't pour without soaking the tablecloth. But the food was good.
Authentic szechuan food
Little bit expensive

Services were great. Very friendly waitresses. The Sichuan dishes are generally good, not top notch, but decent enough. Little bit on the salty side. The fish in the Sichuan peppercorn broth is very flavorful. They also have a full menu of bubble tea and other Chinese sweets/fruity dishes which tracked lots of young Chinese students loving in the area.
Found the secret behind American Chinese food. (For gods sake it is not what real Chinese have everyday)

Awesome food good service only downside they can't sell liquor till their paper work clears up but besides that great place to eat and family friendly they also have a lobster tank

I typed this review right after the meal. Absolutely delicious! Fresh spicy boiled fish filet was delivered in 15 minutes! 15 minutes!!? That's freakin fast even if I was in the restaurant myself. The fish was fresh and well cooked with just the right amount of spices. Just great food. Will order again from here soon.

I went for lunch with a group of colleagues and we all love it.  The lunch specials were very affordable at just $8 for everything and it comes with soup.  I had the hot and sour soup and that was the best part about the lunch.  The main course I had, beef with string beans, and kung pao chicken were   pretty good as well.  I plan to come for dinner and will order a large bowl of those delectable hot and sour soup.  The service was excellent, the ambience was great, and the food was good and authentic.  Their dinner prices is a little high but if the quality of the food for lunch is indicative, I think it's worth it.
Very transitional Sichuan food, the best Sichuan food in Boston area personally.
Big promotion

This restaurant has nice renovated interior and could have become a much better place had the kitchen not used very low quality food ingredients.  The daily special of "spicy fatty beef hot pot" was using lean and tough beef shaving pieces in insufficient quantity for the price.  Another dish with cut pieces of celery included the inedible root part.  The stir fried string beans still had the inedible fibrous string part which is customarily removed for a well made dish.  The service also was sub-par.  We were given only a small glass of water in the beginning and it was never refilled even when I put the empty glass at the edge of the table to attract attention.  A Sichuan spicy food restaurant that doesn't serve ample amount of water?!?  Hope you have a better experience if you do decide to visit.
Great food, friendly and helpful staff.

Really great food and atmosphere.  Chegdu spicy chicken and pork intestine is awesome.

Went there for dinner. Staff was very friendly.  Got the pu pu platter for 2 and everything was great. No issues with that. Didn't eat everything since we are taking food home.  Scallion pancake was crunchy and delicious.  Kung pu chicken was good. A bit on the salty side but overall, still a good choice.  Salty and spicy calarmi was crunchy and delicious.  Pork fried rice was delicious.  Jellyfish was also decilious. A bit different then what you would see in Chinatown but still good. They mix the soy sauce with it instead of dipping the jelly fish into the soy sauce.
Good food little pricy though

I ordered takeout and while it was available very quickly and the food was excellent, it was certainly more than I am used to paying. Rice didn't even come with the main course which was already priced slightly above normal.  Also, when I went in to pick my order up, the front desk was empty and servers walked by me 4 times - one even stood in front of my face cashing a table out - without speaking to me, prior to the host coming to take care of me.  While I'm not happy about that above, again the food was good, and I imagine I'll be coming back here.
Traditional food with a great menu and tenative service.
Tried some take out, quite good. Was a little more than we spend at other places. The presentation and quality offset the cost. The food was much better than average. We'll be coming back.

I ordered a fried rice online, and I said NO CARROT. But it ends up with lots of carrot in my fried rice. I know the guy from front desk may not look at my special requirement carefully, and I don't have time to go back and argue with them. Feel sad.

Had the greatest mothers day experience here the manager Kevin and the two waiters Tim and Ming were awesome....I definitely give this restaurant a 10 for cleanliness, good service, comfortable atmosphere, courteous employees and all around greatness. I would totally recommend and come back again!

Food was authentic, the service was impeccable, and the craft cocktails were better than most high-en bars in Boston. Nothing is better than quality spicy Sichuan food and cold drinks. Highly recommended. Big thanks to the Manager Kevin Le for making it a top notch dining experience.
